description: With a V8, A/C, and shining red color, it's time for you to get your hands on your dream 1966 Ford Mustang for quite an affordable price.

If you're going to have a Mustang, it's hard to beat Candyapple Red.  And if you want to be bold, it's best to have the factory-correct color professional resprayed with a luster-filled modern clearcoat like this one.  It gives you the kind of shine that gets you noticed from across the intersection, and it'll make you the Mustang Guy or Mustang Gal at your local coffee shop.  Of course, this kind of distinction is because you and everyone else really love this total package.  The wraparound chrome bumpers, iconic Mustang corral grille, complete bright trim, and speedy Mag wheels with pony center cap â€“ it all comes together to be part on a timeless American hero.

The first thing that welcomes you when you open the door are the nice black bucket seats with comfort-weave inserts.  The five-dial gauge panel became standard in 1966, which offers a sportier look and holds a complete set of gauges.  A newer AM/FM/cassette stereo head unit blends nicely into the dark dash.  But this is far from a total midnight experience.  The bright trim on the desirable center console, chrome around the gauges, and the three-spoke steering wheel, all lighten up the atmosphere nicely.  Of course, the brightest spot you'll really enjoy is surrounding the vents on the cold-blowing air conditioning.  This just helps makes this classic cruiser comfortable enough for even the daily commute.

Ford's reliable and perky 289 cubic-inch V8 moves the lightweight Mustang enthusiastically through any traffic â€“ especially with the addition of a four-barrel carburetor on top. The engine bay is tidy but not over-detailed, so you shouldn't be afraid to put this one on the road.  These motors are extremely reliable, parts are readily available, and performance is very good, all of which gives you an underlying feeling of carefree classic motoring.  Adding to this go-anywhere sensation in this the three-speed automatic transmission and the modern grip of Firestone Firehawk tires.

Complete with owner's manual, the first-generation Ford Mustang is a true classic car for those who like driving.  They are fun, reliable, and easy to maintain.  Now's your opportunity to pick up a turn-key American icon for a value price.  Call today!!!
